==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zollverein
<hw>Zoll"ve*rein`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., from
<ets>zoll</ets> duty + <ets>verein</ets> union.]</ety> <def>Literally, a
customs union; specifically, applied to the several customs unions
successively formed under the leadership of Prussia among certain German
states for establishing liberty of commerce among themselves and common
tariff on imports, exports, and transit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In 1834 a zollverein was established which included most
of the principal German states except Austria. This was terminated by
the events of 1866, and in 1867 a more closely organized union was
formed, the administration of which was ultimately merged in that of the
new German empire, with which it nearly corresponds
territorially.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zomboruk</ent>⟦br⟧
